  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "6 We thus obtain k output probabilities:",
    "To reliably estimate p, we further need to account for the demonstrations' labels y i: for imbalanced choices of demonstrations (e.g., class imbalance), using the average of p i 's could lead to an underestimation of the probability assigned to infrequent labels.",
    "We therefore compute the average output probabilities p by taking into account the labels y i, as we do for computing BiasScore (§2.3): We first average p i 's associated with the same label ℓ, D ℓ \" tp i | y i \" ℓu, and then set p as the mean of these intra-label averages:",
    "Finally, we use p to compute calibration parameters and score new examples using the same methodology as Zhao et al., 2021 (§3.3).",
    "We refer to our method as Leave-One-Out Calibration (LOOC)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Finally, we use p to compute calibration parameters and score new examples using the same methodology as Zhao et al., 2021 (§3.3)."
  ]
